<xsd:schema attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://schemas.hieos.vangent.com/xdsbridge" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:tns="http://schemas.hieos.vangent.com/xdsbridge"> <xsd:annotation> <xsd:documentation xml:lang="en">This is the schema definition for the HIEOS XDS.b Bridge Service that enables a document source to submit one or more documents to an XDS.b Repository.</xsd:documentation> </xsd:annotation> <xsd:element name="SubmitDocumentRequest"> <xsd:annotation> <xsd:documentation xml:lang="en">The SubmitDocumentRequest element contains the Patient Id, Organization Id and one or more documents for the patient. The Patient and Organization Id are defined with a root (identifier) and extension (assigning authority for the identifier). The extension is optional.</xsd:documentation> </xsd:annotation> <xsd:complexType> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element name="PatientId" type="tns:IdType"/> <xsd:element name="OrganizationId" type="tns:IdType"/> <xsd:element name="Documents" type="tns:DocumentsType"/> </xsd:sequence> </xsd:complexType> </xsd:element> <xsd:complexType name="IdType"> <xsd:attribute name="root" type="xsd:string" use="required"/> <xsd:attribute name="extension" type="xsd:string" use="optional"/> </xsd:complexType> <xsd:complexType name="DocumentsType"> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" name="Document" type="tns:DocumentType"/> </xsd:sequence> </xsd:complexType> <xsd:complexType name="DocumentType"> <xsd:annotation> <xsd:documentation xml:lang="en">The DocumentType element contains the document Type, Id, Replace Id and Content for a document. The Document Type is a coded value indicating the type of document being submitted. The Document Id is a unique identifier for the document. It will be generated if not specified. If a Replace Id is provided, the service will replace the document specified in Replace Id with the submitted document. Content contains the actual document.</xsd:documentation> </xsd:annotation> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element name="Type" type="tns:CodeType"/> <xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="Id" type="xsd:string"/> <xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="ReplaceId" type="xsd:string"/> <xsd:element name="Content" type="xsd:base64Binary"/> </xsd:sequence> </xsd:complexType> <xsd:complexType name="CodeType"> <xsd:attribute name="code" type="xsd:string" use="required"/> <xsd:attribute name="codeSystem" type="xsd:string" use="required"/> <xsd:attribute name="codeSystemName" type="xsd:string" use="optional"/> <xsd:attribute name="displayName" type="xsd:string" use="optional"/> </xsd:complexType> <xsd:element name="SubmitDocumentResponse"> <xsd:annotation> <xsd:documentation xml:lang="en">The SubmitDocumentResponse element indicates if the transaction was successful. If an error occurs then the error details are specified in one or more Error elements. If more than one document is submitted in the request and some documents are processed successfully and some fail then a status of PartialSuccess is returned. The Error Message will indicate which document the error is associated with.</xsd:documentation> </xsd:annotation> <xsd:complexType> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="Errors" type="tns:ErrorsType"/> </xsd:sequence> <xsd:attribute name="status" use="required"> <xsd:simpleType> <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string"> <xsd:enumeration value="Success"/> <xsd:enumeration value="PartialSuccess"/> <xsd:enumeration value="Failure"/> </xsd:restriction> </xsd:simpleType> </xsd:attribute> </xsd:complexType> </xsd:element> <xsd:complexType name="ErrorsType"> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="Error" type="tns:ErrorType"/> </xsd:sequence> </xsd:complexType> <xsd:complexType name="ErrorType"> <xsd:sequence> <xsd:element name="Code" type="xsd:string"/> <xsd:element name="Message" type="xsd:string"/> </xsd:sequence> </xsd:complexType> </xsd:schema>
